  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0dbd\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc0\u0db1 \u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db1\u0db8\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Designates a new forest reserve",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Ministry of Agriculture, Wildlife and Forest Resources Conservation has decided to designate the area around Sampalativu Lagoon in Trincomalee district as a sensitive ecological zone as well as a natural forest reserve.",
        "This decision was taken in a discussion held at the Ministry of Wildlife and Forest Resources Conservation with the participation of the Minister of Agriculture, Wildlife and Forest Resources Conservation Mr. Mahinda Amaraweera.",
        "The surrounding area of \u200b\u200bthe sampling area is also an area with a large mangrove population. But it was revealed in this discussion that the mangrove ecosystem in Trincomalee which was 2043 hectares in the last few years has reduced to 1491 hectares.",
        "Accordingly, it was decided to designate this area of \u200b\u200b239.58 hectares as a sensitive ecological zone and a natural forest reserve around the Sampalativu lagoon belonging to the areas of Sanli, Iluppaikulam, Varodhaya Nagar and Uppuveli Grama Niladhari. The minister instructed the secretary of the ministry, Chandra Herath, to prepare a related cabinet paper."
      ],
